    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Set aside everything you think you know about Shakespeare's masterpiece. Peruvian theatre  company, Teatro LaPlaza’s bold reimagining of Hamlet features eight remarkable actors with Down syndrome who bring fresh energy, sharp humour and deep emotional resonance to Shakespeare’s timeless questions about life and identity. Audiences will experience a moving and joyful celebration of human dignity and creativity that challenges assumptions and redefines a classic for today’s stage."
